Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging. Place onto another lined baking tray, skin-side up, and season with salt and pepper.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the duck is piping hot throughout.

While everything's in the oven, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing).

Season with salt and pepper, then add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and toss together. Set aside.

Once cooked, transfer the duck to a #large bowl{}. Use two #forks{} to shred the duck as finely as you can. Discard the bones.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{64%g}, ensuring the duck is nicely coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

A couple of mins before everything's ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6}(3 per person) into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Transfer the tortillas to your plates. Spread over the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, then fill with the shredded hoisin duck.

Top with the pickled slaw salad and the @crispy onions{1%sachet} - as much as you'd like.

Serve the wedges alongside.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!